data.name: THAI WAH
data.description: THAI WAH is the leader in starch-related solutions in Asia, serving customers in more than 30 countries with the best tapioca, mung bean, rice and other starch and food related products, as well as innovative solutions for clean label, healthy solutions and functional solutions. The company’s core business is divided into tree main categories: the manufacture of tapioca products, vermicelli and noodle products, and bioplastic from tapioca based for local and international distribution. THAI WAH produces premium quality products to satisfy our customers, and is committed to corporate social responsibility (CSR) as a guideline to doing business.

data.description: Rosebrand CASSMAX 26 is a modified tapioca starch, specially formulated to enhance food formulations. This fine white powder brings multiple benefits and features to various food applications. CASSMAXTM 26 serves as a texturizer, further elevating the overall mouthfeel of food products.

data.name: ROSECO® CSB S3
data.description: ROSECO® CSB S3 is a bio-compostable starch compound resin derived from tapioca starch and biopolymers, is characterized by its high bio-content and exceptional mechanical properties, making it well-suited for blown film applications. With warm beige pellets, it provides high toughness and mechanical performance for blown film applications. With a significant renewable material content, CSB S3 effectively reduces the carbon footprint in end products while enhancing functionality and mechanical attributes. It's also easily processed using conventional extrusion machinery.

data.name: ROSEBRAND Organic Tapioca Syrup (GL40A)
data.description: ROSEBRAND Organic Tapioca Syrup (GL40A) is a premium sweetener that brings a touch of natural sweetness to your culinary creations. This tapioca syrup falls under the Sweeteners & Syrups product category, making it an essential ingredient in various food applications. It caters to markets such as bakery, confectionery, desserts & fruit preparations, beverage (juice & juice drinks), dairy, and food processing & packaging. With its nutritive sweetener function, it enhances the taste profile of your food products. Made from plant-origin ingredients, this organic tapioca syrup maintains its natural authenticity. It comes in a convenient liquid form, packaged in drums, totes (IBC), and tanks for easy availability. Enjoy the benefits of this organic sweetener with its sweet taste and certifications, including being Non-GMO, Halal, Kosher, and GMP compliant.

data.name: ROSEBRAND FIBIOCA CF
data.description: Rosebrand FIBIOCA CF is a unique Tapioca-based fiber that combines tapioca starch with insoluble fiber, creating a versatile and beneficial ingredient. Presented as a fine powder with an off-white color, FIBIOCA TM CF offers a range of advantages and features for various applications. As a thickening agent, it adds viscosity and texture to food preparations, enhancing the overall mouthfeel and providing a pulpy texture.

data.name: ROSEBRAND FIBIOCA RS
data.description: Rosebrand FIBIOCA RS is a modified food starch presented as a fine white to off-white powder. As a tapioca-based resistant starch (RS 4), this product offers several advantages for food applications. It serves as a valuable source of dietary fiber, enabling the reduction of caloric content in various food products. Additionally, FIBIOCA TM RS acts as a prebiotic, nourishing beneficial bacteria in the human gut and contributing to overall well-being.

data.name: ROSEBRAND Tapioca Syrup DE 60
data.description: ROSEBRAND Tapioca Syrup DE 60 is a versatile and natural ingredient for various food and nutrition applications. This tapioca syrup serves as a nutritive sweetener, adding a sweet taste to a wide range of products. It finds its application in food categories such as bakery, confectionery, desserts & fruit preparations, and dairy. Additionally, it is used in beverage applications, including juices and powdered mixes. ROSEBRAND Tapioca Syrup DE 60 is known for its high quality and compliance with certifications like FSSC 22000, Halal, Kosher, and Non-GMO. With its liquid form and convenient packaging options including drums, totes (IBC), and tanks, this tapioca syrup is readily available for your manufacturing needs.
